Hebron Technology Co., Ltd. Key Developments

Hebron Technology Co., Ltd. Signs Framework Agreement to Form Joint Venture with Research and Product Complex BioPromin Ltd
Jun 26 17
Hebron Technology Co., Ltd. announced that it has signed a framework cooperation agreement to form a joint venture (JV) with Research and Product Complex BioPromin Ltd. Pursuant to the Agreement executed by and between the Company and BioPromin on June 16, 2017, the parties have agreed to establish the JV to develop, manufacture, and market BioPromin's proprietary noninvasive blood analyzing devices in China. The JV will be based in Konggang New Area, Longgang District, Wenzhou City, Zhejiang Province with registered capital of $5 million and total investment of up to $50 million. Hebron will own 80% of the JV, with BioPromin owning the remaining 20%. BioPromin will also have the right of first refusal to acquire an additional 5% ownership in the JV from Hebron. The formation of the JV is subject to the two parties signing a final definitive agreement, regulatory approvals and other customary closing conditions.


Hebron Technology Co., Ltd. Wins Bid for a Project at Pharmaceutical Company in Tianjin
May 24 17
Hebron Technology Co., Ltd. announced that it has won a bid on the design and implementation of an oil-free compressed air pipe project (the "Project") at a pharmaceutical production facility owned by Tianjin Chase Sun Pharmaceutical Co., Ltd. ("Chase Sun").


Hebron Technology Co., Ltd. Reports Consolidated Earnings Results for the Six Months and Full Year Ended December 31, 2016
Apr 11 17
Hebron Technology Co., Ltd. reported consolidated earnings results for the six months and full year ended December 31, 2016. For the six months, the company reported revenues of $16.4 million against $13.9 million a year ago. Operating income was $5.1 million against $3.9 million a year ago. Net income was $3.8 million against $2.8 million a year ago. Diluted earnings per share were $0.31 against $0.24 a year ago. The increase in total Revenue was related to increase in revenues from both installation service and fluid equipment sales. The increase in operating income was due to the combined effect of an increase in revenues and decrease in operating expenses. 

For the year, the company reported revenues of $27.1 million against $23.0 million a year ago. Operating income was $8.0 million against $6.1 million a year ago. Net income was $5.9 million against $4.4 million a year ago. Basic and diluted earnings per share were $0.49 against $0.37 a year ago. Net cash provided by operating activities was $1.6 million for the year of 2016, compared to $3.9 million for 2015. Income from operations was $7,980,546 against $6,013,345 a year ago. Income before income taxes was $7,937,352 against $6,013,345 a year ago. Acquisitions of property and equipment were $7,667 against $239,917 a year ago.


